 {"id":"bd-17dh","title":"Create Icons utility with Unicode and ASCII fallbacks","description":"# Create Icons utility with Unicode and ASCII fallbacks

## Task Description

Create rch-common/src/ui/icons.rs with an Icons utility that provides Unicode icons with automatic ASCII fallbacks for terminals that dont support Unicode.

## Background

Modern terminals display beautiful Unicode symbols:
- Check marks (✓)
- Cross marks (✗)
- Arrows (→, ←, ↑, ↓)
- Bullets (•, ○, ◉)
- Status indicators (●, ◐, ○)

However, some terminals (especially older ones or certain CI environments) cant display these. We need fallbacks.

## Implementation

```rust
use crate::ui::context::OutputContext;

/// Icons with automatic fallback for non-Unicode terminals
pub struct Icons;

impl Icons {
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // STATUS INDICATORS
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

    /// Success indicator
    pub fn check(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "✓" } else { "[OK]" }
    }

    /// Failure indicator
    pub fn cross(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "✗" } else { "[FAIL]" }
    }

    /// Warning indicator
    pub fn warning(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "⚠" } else { "[WARN]" }
    }

    /// Info indicator
    pub fn info(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "ℹ" } else { "[INFO]" }
    }

    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // WORKER STATUS (filled circle variants)
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

    /// Healthy worker (filled circle)
    pub fn status_healthy(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "●" } else { "[*]" }
    }

    /// Degraded worker (half-filled circle)
    pub fn status_degraded(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "◐" } else { "[~]" }
    }

    /// Unreachable worker (empty circle)
    pub fn status_unreachable(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "○" } else { "[ ]" }
    }

    /// Draining worker (quarter circle)
    pub fn status_draining(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "◑" } else { "[/]" }
    }

    /// Disabled worker (dotted circle)
    pub fn status_disabled(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "◌" } else { "[x]" }
    }

    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // ARROWS AND DIRECTION
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

    /// Right arrow (for flow, assignment)
    pub fn arrow_right(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "→" } else { "->" }
    }

    /// Left arrow
    pub fn arrow_left(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "←" } else { "<-" }
    }

    /// Up arrow (for upload)
    pub fn arrow_up(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "↑" } else { "^" }
    }

    /// Down arrow (for download)
    pub fn arrow_down(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "↓" } else { "v" }
    }

    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // LIST AND BULLET
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

    /// Bullet point
    pub fn bullet(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "•" } else { "*" }
    }

    /// Secondary bullet
    pub fn bullet_hollow(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "○" } else { "o" }
    }

    /// Tree branch
    pub fn tree_branch(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "├" } else { "|" }
    }

    /// Tree end
    pub fn tree_end(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "└" } else { "`" }
    }

    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // ACTIVITY AND PROCESS
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

    /// Worker/computer icon
    pub fn worker(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "🖥" } else { "[W]" }
    }

    /// Compilation/build icon
    pub fn compile(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "🔨" } else { "[C]" }
    }

    /// Transfer/package icon
    pub fn transfer(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "📦" } else { "[T]" }
    }

    /// Clock/time icon
    pub fn clock(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "⏱" } else { "[T]" }
    }

    /// Gear/settings icon
    pub fn gear(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "⚙" } else { "[G]" }
    }

    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // SLOT VISUALIZATION (for worker slots)
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

    /// Filled slot (in use)
    pub fn slot_filled(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "█" } else { "#" }
    }

    /// Empty slot (available)
    pub fn slot_empty(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "░" } else { "-" }
    }

    /// Partial slot (for progress)
    pub fn slot_partial(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "▓" } else { "=" }
    }

    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // PROGRESS BAR CHARACTERS
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

    /// Progress bar filled
    pub fn progress_filled(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "━" } else { "=" }
    }

    /// Progress bar empty
    pub fn progress_empty(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "─" } else { "-" }
    }

    /// Progress bar head
    pub fn progress_head(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "╸" } else { ">" }
    }

    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // MISC
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════

    /// Lightning bolt (for speed)
    pub fn lightning(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "⚡" } else { "!" }
    }

    /// Light bulb (for tips/suggestions)
    pub fn lightbulb(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "💡" } else { "TIP:" }
    }

    /// Lock (for reserved/locked)
    pub fn lock(ctx: OutputContext) -> &'static str {
        if ctx.supports_unicode() { "🔒" } else { "[L]" }
    }
}
```

## Usage Example

```rust
use crate::ui::{context::OutputContext, icons::Icons};

fn print_worker_status(name: &str, healthy: bool) {
    let ctx = OutputContext::detect();
    let icon = if healthy {
        Icons::check(ctx)
    } else {
        Icons::cross(ctx)
    };
    eprintln!("  {} {}", icon, name);
}
```

## Testing

```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;

    #[test]
    fn test_icons_with_unicode() {
        let ctx = OutputContext::Interactive; // Assume unicode support

        // These should return Unicode characters
        assert!(Icons::check(ctx).len() > 1 || Icons::check(ctx) == "✓");
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_icons_fallback() {
        let ctx = OutputContext::Plain; // No unicode

        // These should return ASCII fallbacks
        assert!(Icons::check(ctx).chars().all(|c| c.is_ascii()));
        assert!(Icons::cross(ctx).chars().all(|c| c.is_ascii()));
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_all_icons_return_non_empty() {
        let ctx = OutputContext::Interactive;

        assert!(!Icons::check(ctx).is_empty());
        assert!(!Icons::cross(ctx).is_empty());
        assert!(!Icons::warning(ctx).is_empty());
        // ... all icons
    }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

1. [ ] All icon methods defined with Unicode and ASCII variants
2. [ ] OutputContext correctly determines which to use
3. [ ] ASCII fallbacks are readable and meaningful
4. [ ] All icons return non-empty strings
5. [ ] Unit tests pass

