+{"id":"bd-1nk5","title":"EPIC: Error Handling and User Messaging","description":"# Error Handling and User Messaging

## Overview
RCH has an excellent error infrastructure using miette for rich diagnostics. However, not all error paths use it consistently, leading to user-unfriendly error messages in some cases.

## Current State

### Strong Points
- Proper error types in rch/src/error.rs with miette Diagnostic
- Error codes follow RCH-Exxx convention
- Rich help text with remediation suggestions

### Problems Found
There are ~35 `bail\!()` calls in commands.rs that bypass the structured error system:

```rust
// Line 2167 - No error code, no context, no remediation
bail\!("rch-wkr not found on remote");

// Line 2197 - Same problem  
bail\!("rustup install failed: {}", stderr.trim());

// Line 2943 - Generic error
bail\!("rustup install failed: {}", stderr.trim());
```

These plain string errors:
1. Have no error code for scripting/automation
2. Provide no remediation steps
3. Don't indicate which worker/host failed
4. Can't be programmatically parsed

## Error Code Gaps
Current codes have gaps suggesting incomplete coverage:
- E001-E004: Config (has E005-E006 gap)
- E007-E009: Worker 
- E100-E108: SSH (has gaps)
- E202, E204, E207: Worker health (missing E203, E205, E206)
- No E300+ category defined for build errors

## Key Files
- rch/src/error.rs - Error type definitions
- rch/src/commands.rs - Where most bail\!() calls live
- rch-common/src/ui/error.rs - ErrorPanel display

## Success Criteria
- Every user-facing error has an RCH-Exxx code
- Every error includes actionable remediation steps
- Error codes are documented in a public reference
- No bare bail\!() calls without structured context","status":"closed","priority":4,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-01-28T04:58:56.426351214Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-31T18:24:13.148439005Z","closed_at":"2026-01-31T18:22:02.105523989Z","close_reason":"All bail!() calls converted to structured errors. Added WebError (E900-E902), CompletionError (E910-E911), EditorError (E920-E921), and HookError::NotImplemented. All quality gates pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"comments":[{"id":108,"issue_id":"bd-1nk5","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Phase 1 complete (VioletBarn): Added PlatformError (E600-E603), BinaryError (E800-E803), FleetError (E700-E704) to rch/src/error.rs. Updated test ranges. Next: Convert bail!() calls to use these types.","created_at":"2026-01-30T22:42:34Z"},{"id":120,"issue_id":"bd-1nk5","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"IvoryBridge: Converted last bail!() in config_edit to use EditorError::ExitedWithError (RCH-E920)","created_at":"2026-01-31T18:14:56Z"},{"id":121,"issue_id":"bd-1nk5","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"IvoryBridge: Converted bail!() in completions.rs to CompletionError::UnsupportedShell (RCH-E910)","created_at":"2026-01-31T18:16:32Z"},{"id":122,"issue_id":"bd-1nk5","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"agent/hook.rs: converted 4 bail!() calls to HookError::NotSupported (E506) and HookError::NotImplemented (E507). All bail!() calls in rch/src are now converted to structured errors.","created_at":"2026-01-31T18:19:34Z"},{"id":123,"issue_id":"bd-1nk5","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"VioletCreek: Verified no bail!() calls remain in rch/src. Converted fleet/ssh.rs (2 calls to FleetError::UnexpectedOutput), fleet/executor.rs (2 calls to SshError::ConnectionFailed and FleetError::HealthCheckFailed), fleet/rollback.rs (3 calls to FleetError::NoBackupAvailable and FleetError::RollbackFailed), fleet/mod.rs (1 call to BinaryError::NotFound). Added HookError::NotSupported (E506